msgstr "Suppose there was a billabong that had been stagnant for many years. "

msgctxt "an4.178:4.6"
msgid "Tassā puriso yāni ceva āyamukhāni tāni vivareyya, yāni ca apāyamukhāni tāni pidaheyya, devo ca sammā dhāraṃ anuppaveccheyya. "
msgstr "And someone was to open up the inlets and close off the drains, and the heavens provided plenty of rain. "

msgctxt "an4.178:4.7"
msgid "Evañhi tassā, bhikkhave, jambāliyā āḷippabhedo pāṭikaṅkho. "
msgstr "You’d expect that billabong to break its banks. "

msgctxt "an4.178:4.8"
msgid "Evamevaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu aññataraṃ santaṃ cetovimuttiṃ upasampajja viharati. "
msgstr "In the same way, take a mendicant who enters and remains in a certain peaceful release of the heart. "

msgctxt "an4.178:4.9"
msgid "So avijjāppabhedaṃ manasi karoti. "
msgstr "They focus on smashing ignorance, "

msgctxt "an4.178:4.10"
msgid "Tassa avijjāppabhedaṃ manasi karoto avijjāppabhede cittaṃ pakkhandati pasīdati santiṭṭhati adhimuccati. "
msgstr "and their mind is eager, confident, settled, and decided about it. "

msgctxt "an4.178:4.11"
msgid "Tassa kho evaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhuno avijjāppabhedo pāṭikaṅkho. "
msgstr "You’d expect that mendicant to smash ignorance. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an4.178:4.12"
msgid "Ime kho, bhikkhave, cattāro puggalā santo saṃvijjamānā lokasmin”ti. "
msgstr "These are the four people found in the world.” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an4.178:4.13"
msgid "Aṭṭhamaṃ. "
msgstr ""

